                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.6363 ST 2/206: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-12-13T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 13, 1937—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>38. Your 78, December 12, noon. Does the decision of the Junta mean that the
                    Bolivian Government has refused the extension of time that was the subject of
                    the Department’s 30, November 13, 7 p.m.?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
